Round 2 update. Please review docs/plans/eden-phase-8a-wire-protocol.md again. Changes this round:

1. Read-back reconciliation is now strict: only three outcomes — confirmed success (observed SHA == expected), confirmed divergence (observed SHA != expected, raise AtomicityViolation, do NOT compensate), or IndeterminateIntegration. Null trial_commit_sha on read-back is explicitly called out as NOT positive proof of non-commit and resolves to IndeterminateIntegration, not compensate. The Integrator compensates ONLY on a non-transport store error that the server demonstrably rejected.

2. Retry guidance for non-idempotent mutations (claim/reject/reclaim/accept) is narrowed: the blanket 'illegal-transition = prior call committed' convention is removed. Plan now states 8a does not standardize an HTTP-level retry convention for these; the StoreClient raises IndeterminateRequest and the caller decides per-operation. Future phase may add Idempotency-Key.

3. Different-SHA integrate_trial error pinned as eden://error/invalid-precondition (HTTP 409). Chapter text and test section now agree.

4. Stale refs fixed: 'FastAPI (or Starlette; see Open questions)' → 'FastAPI'; algorithm section now calls GET /_reference/tasks/{id}/validate-terminal.

Please check the atomicity story holds under concurrent reconciliation and that the retry guidance is appropriately scoped.
