 succeeded in 0ms:
   540	- `eden-dispatch.run_experiment` needs no signature change; it
   541	  already accepts a `Store` and an `integrate_trial` callable. A
   542	  `StoreClient` *is* a `Store`, so the driver works unchanged.
   543	- `eden-git.Integrator` gains one new failure mode —
   544	  `IndeterminateIntegration` — raised when a wire-mediated
   545	  `integrate_trial` call's outcome cannot be determined. Direct-
   546	  `Store` callers never see it (no transport involved); wire-
   547	  mediated callers treat it as operator-intervention territory,
   548	  same as `AtomicityViolation`. Existing exception handlers in
   549	  `eden-dispatch` propagate it without special handling because
   550	  `run_experiment` currently doesn't catch integrator errors.
   551	- The `StoreClient.integrate_trial` wrapper owns the
   552	  transport-indeterminate reconciliation (read-back + retry loop)
   553	  described in "Atomicity and composite-commit handling" above.
   554	  The Integrator sees either a successful return, a definite
   555	  failure it can compensate, or an `IndeterminateIntegration` it
   556	  must re-raise — the same three-way decision it would have in a
   557	  direct-`Store` world, with the client absorbing the HTTP
   558	  complexity.
   559	- `Store.integrate_trial` server endpoint must preserve the §3.4
   560	  invariant: the HTTP handler invokes the same atomic transaction
   561	  the direct call does, and adds same-value idempotency on top
   562	  (no-op if `trial_commit_sha` already equals the request value;
   563	  error if it equals a different value). The same-value
   564	  idempotency also applies to the direct-`Store` path, so
   565	  `Store.integrate_trial` gains this behavior uniformly (the
   566	  `_check_idempotent` helper in `Integrator` already expressed
   567	  the same rule externally; moving the same-value check down into
   568	  `Store.integrate_trial` keeps the HTTP binding's contract and
   569	  the direct-call contract identical).
   570	- Existing tests that construct `Store` directly stay. The
   571	  parametrized fixtures gain an additional `ClientStore` backend;
   572	  no direct-`Store` test is removed.
